% Python Code Ontology - CNL Format
% Natural English syntax for semantic code analysis
%
% This ontology extends the OO meta-ontology (oo_ontology.cnl) with
% Python-specific concepts. All py:* types are subclasses of oo:* types,
% enabling language-independent queries using the oo: prefix.

% ============================================================================
% Class Hierarchy (Python-specific)
% ============================================================================

Every `py:Method` is a `py:Function`.

% ============================================================================
% Meta-Ontology Integration (extends oo_ontology.cnl)
% ============================================================================

Every `py:Module` is a `oo:Module`.

Every `py:Class` is a `oo:Class`.

Every `py:Function` is a `oo:Function`.

Every `py:Method` is a `oo:Method`.

Every `py:Parameter` is a `oo:Parameter`.

Every `py:Import` is a `oo:Import`.

Every `py:Assignment` is a `oo:Assignment`.

Every `py:Attribute` is a `oo:Field`.

Every `py:Reference` is a `oo:Reference`.

% ============================================================================
% Exception Handling (extends oo_ontology.cnl)
% ============================================================================

Every `py:TryBlock` is a `oo:TryBlock`.

Every `py:ExceptHandler` is a `oo:CatchClause`.

Every `py:FinallyBlock` is a `oo:FinallyClause`.

Every `py:TryElseBlock` is a `oo:Statement`.

% ============================================================================
% Statements (extends oo_ontology.cnl)
% ============================================================================

Every `py:RaiseStatement` is a `oo:ThrowStatement`.

Every `py:ReturnStatement` is a `oo:ReturnStatement`.

Every `py:WithStatement` is a `oo:Statement`.

% ============================================================================
% Type Hierarchy
% ============================================================================

Every `py:int` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:str` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:bool` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:float` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:list` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:dict` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:set` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:tuple` is a `py:Type`.
Every `py:None` is a `py:Type`.
